UNDIAGNOSED DEATH - RUSSIA (BASHKIRIYA): REQUEST FOR INFO
*********************************************************
A ProMED-mail post
<http://www.promedmail.org>
Date: Wed, 13 Sep 2000 11:23:41 -0400
From: Marjorie P. Pollack <pollackmp@mindspring.com>
Source: ITAR/TASS News Agency, filed: Wed 13 Sep 2000 8:41 AM ES [edited]

Unidentified virus kills child in the Republic of Bashkiriya
------------------------------------------------------------
A 5-year-old child died on Mon 11 Sep 2000 of lung edema and 30 other
children aged 3 to 7 were taken to hospital in the Russian Republic of
Bashkiriya in the Urals. The incident in a children's holiday centre
occurred on 11 Sep 2000, but medical services [did not report the incident]
until 13 Sep 2000. According to preliminary information, the virus causes
laryngotracheitis.
--
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>
[Information on the cause and further progress of this outbreak would be
welcomed. In the absence of additional information, it should not be
assumed that the causative agent is a virus. - Mod.CP]
